              <title>About SCoPE Seminars</title>
              <link>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/4725</link>
              <guid>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/4725</guid>
              <description><![CDATA[<p><img src="http://scope.bccampus.ca/file.php/9/SCoPE_logos/Web/SCoPE01.jpg alt=" alt="" /></p>
<p>SCoPE is an online community hosted by BCcampus in British Columbia, Canada. The core activity in SCoPE is scheduled seminar discussions facilitated  by volunteers. This is a tradition that began with the Global Educators' Network in 1999 as part of the TeleLearning Network of Centres of Excellence. At SCoPE we also host special interest groups (SIGs) by request,  online conferences, and special projects as they emerge. Ideas for  seminar discussion topics and other SCoPE activities emerge through participation in the communitiy.</p>
<p>SCoPE seminars are free and open to the public. We attempt to cater to busy professionals. In that sense, there is no registration process for seminars and members are free to participate according to their own time and interests. We welcome participation on the periphery through the Web and RSS; no login is required.</p>]]></description>
